paragraphs: Red wine is the most popular kind of wine in the world. Made from fermented grapes, it is produced by crushing the grapes and pressing them to extract their juice. We're confident that you'll find your favourite red wine brands like Penfolds, Grant Burge, Jacob’s Creek and many more from our carefully selected range.

campaigns.text2:
Buy Red Wine Near You or Online

Explore the world of great red wine with labels from European powerhouses such as Bosio and Campo Viejo and exciting new world wines like Vistamar, as well as red wine in Australia like Penfolds from South Australia and Dexter. Many red wine styles such as Shiraz, Pinot Noir, Merlot and Malbec are on offer, and our knowledgeable staff can help you choose. We’ve been sourcing and selling red wine for over 20 years so you’ve come to a place you can trust.

Choosing your next red wine has never been easier, with options to visit in store, buy red wine online with our free click & collect service, or simply select red wine delivery. Yes, we deliver red wine to Sydney, Melbourne, Perth and everywhere in between.

Red Wine Serving Suggestions

Red wine is often served chilled and is usually accompanied with a meal. A wine such as a Shiraz is the ideal with roasted or grilled meats such as beef or venison or just a simple burger on the BBQ, as well as hard cheeses such as cheddar and parmesan. Red wine flavours work wonders with this type of food.

Best Food to Pair with Red Wine

  • Hard Cheeses
  • Roasted Meats

FAQs from Red Wine Buyers

Q. What is the cost of cheapest red wine?

Our lowest price for a 700ml bottle is $4.

Q. Does South Australia have the best red wine?

There are many wine regions in Australia that make excellent red wine, but yes South Australia does have some of the world's best.

Q. Which brand is best for red wine?

Penfolds is considered one of the truly great red wines.

Q. Which red wine type is the best for cooking?

Merlot and Pinot Noir to name a few.
